014-02-25 00:31:51','',238,'http://secularstudents.org.uiowa.edu/238-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(347,2,'2014-02-24 19:03:26','2014-02-25 01:03:26','SecSI stands for Secular Students at Iowa. We are affiliated with the Secular Student Alliance, and an official student organization at the University of Iowa.\r\nOur group revolves around four core principles:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Advocacy:</strong> This organization stresses the importance of critical thinking and skepticism. As such, this organization will promote these standpoints through events and discussion.<br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Community:</strong> This group strives to be a safe space for non-theists and theists with doubts to come together and express their views, ideas, and perspectives.<br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Education:</strong> This group wishes to educate others both outside and within the group about scientific and critical thinking, secular values, and non-theistic worldviews.<br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Service:</strong> The members of this organization hold that it is important to maintain a community that recognizes the value of life itself. As such, volunteer work is an important activity to maintain a healthy community and world. This group strives to conduct service and charity work.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nYou can see our constitution <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/os_uploads/446315_Constitution%20for%20SecSIDraft3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here in full</a>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<h3>Meetings:</h3>\r\n<p>We normally meet in the Minnesota Room of the Iowa Memorial Union in Iowa City, at 6pm for our general meetings. Check the events page for the most up-to-date meeting and event details.<p>\r\n<h3>Membership:</h3>\r\nIn order to become a member, the person may either:\r\n1) purchase SecSI apparel at the beginning of the semester - which grants membership for the current academic school year\r\n\r\nor, 2) pay a $5 membership due at the start of each semester. These options will only be available at the start of each semester.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re a part of the University of Iowa Community and want to get in touch about becoming a member, use the form at the bottom of this page!\r\n<h3>Organizers:</h3>\r\nAn organizer is a SecSI member whose job is to keep the group meetings running, plan group events, be a representative for the group, and conduct other formal duties.\r\n<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>Social Media</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"one-third column\"><a class=\"twitter-timeline\" href=\"https://twitter.com/UISecs\" data-widget-id=\"425776999278186496\">Tweets by @UISecs</a>\r\n<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");</script>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"one-half column\"><iframe src=\"//www.facebook.com/plugins/likebox.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fsecsi&amp;width&amp;height=590&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;show_faces=true&amp;header=true&amp;stream=true&amp;show_border=true&amp;appId=470713492967451\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"overflow:hidden; height:350px; border-bottom: solid black 1px;\" allowTransparency=\"false\" ></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h4>Use this form to contact the SecSI Organizers about anything!</h4>\r\n[contact-form][contact-field label=\'Name\' type=\'name\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Email\' type=\'email\' required=\'1\'/][contact-field label=\'Comment\' type=\'textarea\' required=\'1\'/][/contact-form]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About SecSI','','inherit','open','open','','191-revision-v1','','','2014-02-24 19:03:26','2014-02-25 01:03:26','',191,'http://secularstudents.org.uiowa.edu/191-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(348,2,'2014-02-24 22:25:00','2014-02-25 04:25:00','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://secularstuden